egory Patrikareas]] |- | style="padding-right:9px; text-align:right;"| 7 | [[Eleftherios Venizelos]] [[File:Ελευθέριος Βενιζέλος.jpg|100px]] | Prime Minister (1910-1915) (1917-1920) (1924) (1928-1932) (1932) (1933). Most often re-elected Prime Minister of the country. Introduced many constitutional and economic reforms which modernized Greek society. | [[Petros Tatsopoulos]] |- | style="padding-right:9px; text-align:right;"| 8 | [[Ioannis Kapodistrias]] [[File:Kapodistrias2.jpg|100px]] | President. First president of independent Greece (1827-1831). | [[Thanos Veremis]] |- | style="padding-right:9px; text-align:right;"| 9 | [[Plato]] [[File:Plato Silanion Musei Capitolini MC1377.jpg|100px]] | Philosopher. Founder of [[Platonism]]. One of the most influential thinkers in history. | [[Pemy Zouni]] |- | style="padding-right:9px; text-align:right;"| 10 | [[Pericles]] [[File:Pericles Townley BM 549 n2.jpg|100px]] | King and general. Won many decisive victories during the [[Greco-Persian Wars]] and [[Peloponnesian War]]s and laid the foundation of the [[Athenian democracy]]. During his regime arts and science blossomed. | [[Tasos Telloglou]] |}
