{{Infobox politician | name = Ángela Covadonga Bachiller | image = | caption = | birth_date = | birth_place = [[Spain]] | death_date = | death_place = | constituency = [[Valladolid]], [[Spain]] | office = Town councillor | term = | predecessor = Jesús García Galván <ref name="elpais1">{{cite web|url=http://elpais.com/elpais/2013/08/08/inenglish/1375970149_703675.html |title=Valladolid appoints Spain’s first Down Syndrome councillor &#124; In English &#124; EL PAÍS |website=Elpais.com |date= |accessdate=2016-04-13}}</ref> | successor = | party =[[People's Party (Spain)|People's Party]] | religion = | spouse = | children = | website = | footnotes = | date = 29 July | year = 2013 | source = }}
'''Ángela Covadonga Bachiller''' is a Spanish [[city councillor]] for [[Valladolid]] and a member of the [[People's Party (Spain)|People's Party]]. She became Spain's first city councillor with [[Down syndrome]], sworn in on 29 July 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ldascotland.org/index.php/information/29-new-councillor-with-downs-syndrome-elected-in-spain |title=New Councillor with Downs Syndrome elected in Spain |website=Ldascotland.org |date=2013-07-29 |accessdate=2016-04-13}}</ref> Bachiller had previously worked for two and a half years at Valladolid City Hall as an administrative assistant. She had the opportunity to stand when a fellow People's Party member politician stood down.<ref name="elpais1"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.downsyndromedaily.com/2013/08/first-councilwoman-with-down-syndrome.html |title=Spanish Angela Bachiller first councilwoman with Down syndrome |publisher=Down Syndrome Daily |date=2013-08-14 |accessdate=2016-04-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.downsyndromedaily.com/2013/08/first-councilwoman-with-down-syndrome.html?m=1 |title=Spanish Angela Bachiller first councilwoman with Down syndrome |publisher=Down Syndrome Daily |date=2013-08-14 |accessdate=2016-04-13}}</ref>
Mayor Francisco Javier León de la Riva described Bachiller as "an example of strength and of someone overcoming obstacles",<ref name="thelocal1">{{cite web|url=http://www.thelocal.es/20130801/i-want-to-be-an-honest-politician |title='I want to be an honest politician' - The Local |website=Thelocal.es |date=2013-08-01 |accessdate=2016-04-13}}</ref> while her boss in Valladolid's social welfare department, Rosa Hernández, said: "The most important thing is that her family didn't overprotect her. She's tenacious and capable of carrying out her work at all times."<ref name="thelocal1"/>
The opposition Socialist Party (PSOE) supports Bachiller's appointment. "We see this as something perfectly normal" says Óscar Puente, the head of the Socialist Group in Valladolid City Council. "Let's hope that it encourages other people in her situation to play a bigger role in society."<ref name="elpais1"/>
